WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Do you know why most transformation projects
in companies fail?

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.500
Because companies integrate technology
without adapting the brain — and face resistance.

00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:13.000
Today, organizations invest millions in AI.
They build new systems.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:17.000
They design new processes. But employees
show resistance.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:21.500
Leaders revert to old decision-making habits.
Teams struggle with uncertainty.

00:00:21.500 --> 00:00:25.000
In other words, behavior doesn't change.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:30.000
Yet with neuroscience-based applications,
lasting behavioral change is possible.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Because what drives transformation is not technology —
it is the brain's capacity for adaptation.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:40.000
The brain can perceive change as a threat,
reduce decision quality under cognitive load.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:45.000
And revert to old behavioral patterns
in the face of uncertainty.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:50.000
That's why tomorrow's successful companies
won't just be those investing in technology...

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:56.000
They'll be those who understand human behavior,
decision-making processes, and learning mechanisms.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:01.000
We approach this from a different angle:
We design the transformation architecture

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:05.500
of the business world through brain science
and artificial intelligence.

00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:10.500
Because tomorrow's competitive advantage lies not in technology,
but in understanding the human brain that uses it.

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:16.000
What do you think — can we design
the future without knowing the brain?
